### 📘 Day 25 of 90 Days of Reinforcement Learning

**🎯 Topic: Policy Optimization & Stability Problems in RL**

After learning how value functions are approximated with neural networks, today I focused on a key question:

**Why do policy-based methods need special care during optimization?**

---

### 🔍 What I learned today:

• Directly optimizing policies can be **unstable**
• Large policy updates can **collapse performance**
• High variance gradients slow down learning
• Exploration–exploitation balance becomes tricky

---

### ⚠️ Common Problems in Policy Optimization:

• **High variance** in gradient estimates
• **Destructive updates** (policy changes too much in one step)
• **Poor sample efficiency**
• **Training instability** in deep RL

---

### 💡 Why this matters:

These challenges are the **main reason modern RL algorithms exist**.

Algorithms like:

* PPO
* TRPO
* SAC

are all designed to **control policy updates and improve stability**.

👉 Understanding *why* vanilla policy gradients struggle makes it much easier to understand *why* PPO works.

---

### 🧠 Big Picture:

> Stable policy optimization is the bridge between theory-level RL and real-world, scalable Deep RL systems.

